# Skill: Discussion & Conclusion Writing

## Discussion paragraph template
1. Restate the key finding (different wording from results)
2. Why does this happen? (architectural / data / linguistic reason)
3. Comparison with prior work — does this agree or contradict?
4. Implication for the field

## Limitations — be specific
NOT: "Our dataset is small and future work could expand it."
YES: "The dataset currently covers a single book series
(Yorùbá di Wúrà), limiting font diversity. Books with older
typesetting conventions or handwritten elements are not represented."

## Future work — make it concrete
- Scaling to Igbo and Hausa (Ajami script)
- OCR + language model correction pipeline
- Synthetic data augmentation for rare diacritic combinations
- Dialectal variation (Standard vs regional Yorùbá)

## Conclusion structure (max 1 paragraph)
Contribution 1 -> Contribution 2 -> Contribution 3 -> broader impact.
No new information. No "in this paper we have shown."

## Sovereign Intelligence framing (for DLI alignment)
In the final paragraph, connect to African language sovereignty:
this benchmark enables African researchers to build, evaluate,
and own OCR infrastructure for their own languages.
